[1] Ukraine (update)
Date: Wed 25 Jan 2012
Source: UN.UA [In Russian, machine translation, edited]
http://un.ua/rus/article/371979.html

Review of measles in Ukraine
------------------------
The Sanitary-Epidemiological Service (SES)has registered 1952 cases of suspected measles cases in Ukraine between 1 and 25 Jan 2012. Between 24 and 25 Jan 2012 a total of 154 cases were identified. In particular, in the Lviv region between 1 and 25 Jan 2012 a total of 967 cases of suspected measles virus infection have been recorded with 64 cases reported between 24 and 25 January. The corresponding figures for Ivano-Frankivsk are534 (42), for Rivne - 124 (14), for Carpathian - 103 (12 ), for Ternopil - 54 (7), and for Volyn - 40 (3). In Kiev, between 1 and 25 Jan 2012 there were 12 cases, including one case between 24 and 25 Jan 2012.

In other administrative territories of Ukraine only sporadic cases of suspected measles (totalling 118) have been registered since the beginning of 2012. Between 1 and 16 Jan 2012 the SES has registered 983 cases of suspected measles cases in Ukraine. By contrast during the whole of 2011 throughout the whole of Ukraine only 1513 suspected cases of measles were registered. In the Lviv region in mid-December 2011 a single measles fatality was recorded, the first in the region during the past 5 years. The current outbreak is being attributed to to the significantly increased measles morbidity throughout Europe in general.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS <promed@promedmail.org>

[A map showing the regions of Ukraine can be accessed at: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administrative_divisions_of_Ukraine. - Mod.CP]


