The Americas
----------
[2] Ecuador
Date: Tue 24 Jan 2012
Source: Hoy, Ecuador [In Spanish, machine translation, abbrev. & edited - Mod.CP]
http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/identificados-203-casos-de-sarampion-en-todo-el-pais-530447.html

Update
------
Two days after the completion of the vaccination campaign against measles, the Ministry of Health (MOH) said yesterday that it had identified a total of 203 cases of measlesacross the country. A total of 120 cases have tested positive for measles and 83 appear to be epidemiologically linked.

The Ministry stated that the province of Tungurahua had recorded a total of 131 cases. The remaining cases were distributed as follows; 28 cases in the province of Pichincha, 17 cases in Guayas,16 in Pastaza, and 8 cases in Chimborazo Cotopaxi.

An official also reported that the most affected age group is still the under 5 years group. "This trend has continued throughout the period of the outbreak," he said.

On 5 Jan 2012 the MOH reported that in order to protect more children and teenagers, aged 6 months to 14 years, the vaccination campaign against measles would run until 22 Jan 2012.

The official stated that the Expanded Program on Immunisation would have achieved a vaccination coverage against measles of from 104% [?]of children aged between 6 months and 4 years, and 75% of children and adolescents 5 to 14 years of age. "The vaccination campaign against measles will have protected 1 331 951 children under 5, and 165 100 children and adolescents aged from 5 to 14 years",

--
Reported by:
ProMED-ESP <proned@promedmail.org>

