[3] USA (Delaware)
Date: Fri 27 Jan 2012
Source: Health Check [edited]
http://abclocal.go.com/wpvi/story?section=news/health&id=8522260&rss=rss-wpvi-article-8522260

Measles case confirmed in Delaware child
-----------------------------------
Public health officials say a case of measles has been confirmed in a 6-year-old Clayton girl. The Division of Public Health (DPH) says the illness was diagnosed by the child's doctor on 13 Jan 2012 and lab tests confirmed it on 23 Jan 2012. The girl was not hospitalized and she has not suffered any complications.
Officials say the child's school, Caravel Academy, has been notified.

DPH has only confirmed five cases of measles in Delaware since 1995.

--
